        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Simple Linear Regression {#sec-simple}\n",
        "\n",
        "## Model Specification\n",
        "\n",
        "We regress **miles per gallon** (`mpg`) on **weight** (`wt`).\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\text{mpg}_i = \\beta_0 + \\beta_1 \\cdot \\text{wt}_i + \\varepsilon_i\n",
        "$$"
      ],
      "id": "fdf88950"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: slr-model\n",
        "\n",
        "model_slr = smf.ols(\"mpg ~ wt\", data=mtcars).fit()\n",
        "print(model_slr.summary())"
      ],
      "id": "slr-model",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Interpreting the Output\n",
        "\n",
        "| Term | Estimate | Interpretation |\n",
        "|------|----------|----------------|\n",
        "| Intercept | ~37.29 | Expected `mpg` when `wt = 0` (extrapolation) |\n",
        "| `wt` | ~−5.34 | Each additional 1,000 lbs → mpg drops by ~5.34 |\n",
        "\n",
        "> **R² ≈ 0.75**: Weight alone explains ~75% of the variance in fuel efficiency.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Scatter Plot with Regression Line"
      ],
      "id": "132f312c"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: slr-plot\n",
        "#| fig-cap: 'Simple Linear Regression: mpg ~ wt'\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
        "ax.scatter(mtcars[\"wt\"], mtcars[\"mpg\"], color=\"#4C72B0\", alpha=0.7, edgecolors=\"white\", s=70)\n",
        "\n",
        "x_range = np.linspace(mtcars[\"wt\"].min(), mtcars[\"wt\"].max(), 100)\n",
        "y_pred  = model_slr.params[\"Intercept\"] + model_slr.params[\"wt\"] * x_range\n",
        "ax.plot(x_range, y_pred, color=\"#DD4444\", linewidth=2, label=\"OLS fit\")\n",
        "\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Weight (1000 lbs)\")\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel(\"Miles per Gallon\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"mpg ~ wt\")\n",
        "ax.legend()\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "slr-plot",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Multiple Linear Regression {#sec-multiple}\n",
        "\n",
        "## Model Specification\n",
        "\n",
        "We add **horsepower** (`hp`) and **number of cylinders** (`cyl`) as predictors.\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\text{mpg}_i = \\beta_0 + \\beta_1\\,\\text{wt}_i + \\beta_2\\,\\text{hp}_i + \\beta_3\\,\\text{cyl}_i + \\varepsilon_i\n",
        "$$"
      ],
      "id": "a317f809"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: mlr-model\n",
        "\n",
        "model_mlr = smf.ols(\"mpg ~ wt + hp + cyl\", data=mtcars).fit()\n",
        "print(model_mlr.summary())"
      ],
      "id": "mlr-model",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Coefficient Plot"
      ],
      "id": "67ef7e90"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: coef-plot\n",
        "#| fig-cap: Coefficient plot with 95% confidence intervals\n",
        "\n",
        "coefs = model_mlr.params.drop(\"Intercept\")\n",
        "conf  = model_mlr.conf_int().drop(\"Intercept\")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 3))\n",
        "ax.errorbar(\n",
        "    coefs, coefs.index,\n",
        "    xerr=[coefs - conf[0], conf[1] - coefs],\n",
        "    fmt=\"o\", color=\"#4C72B0\", capsize=5, linewidth=1.5\n",
        ")\n",
        "ax.axvline(0, linestyle=\"--\", color=\"gray\", linewidth=1)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Coefficient Estimate\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Multiple Regression Coefficients (95% CI)\")\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "coef-plot",
